Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: add combined lambda + atomic-isolation + constexpr
 test

A constexpr lambda captures by reference and mutates a compact struct whose atomic field is isolated to its own cache line. The lambda accesses a member at the reordered offset and constant evaluation yields the right value, proving the isolated layout is consistent across capture, member access, and constexpr evaluation.



diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-lambda-over-isolated-atomic.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-lambda-over-isolated-atomic.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..d86bf1829
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-lambda-over-isolated-atomic.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@
+// HARD (combined lambda + atomic isolation + constexpr): a constexpr lambda
+// captures by reference and mutates a compact struct whose atomic field is
+// isolated onto its own 64-byte cache line. The lambda reads/writes a member at
+// the reordered offset and constant evaluation produces the right value --
+// proving the isolated layout is consistent across capture, member access, and
+// constexpr evaluation.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -verify %s
+// expected-no-diagnostics
+
+compact struct S {
+  char tag;
+  _Atomic int a; // isolated onto its own cache line
+  int b;
+};
+
+constexpr int run() {
+  S s{};
+  auto inc = [&s](int d) {
+    s.b += d;
+    return s.b;
+  };
+  inc(3);
+  return inc(4);
+}
+
+static_assert(run() == 7, "lambda mutates the reordered/isolated struct");
